      "message": "Do you want to be this heavy-handed?\n\nAt first, I thought “yeah, because it’ll make it painfully obvious that upload is broken.” But this will really only be happening in the handler process. A handler CHECK shouldn’t cause any visible brokenness in the browser. So really, this just winds up killing off the handler so that we can’t collect any reports at all.\n\nIt might be better to replace the CHECK with a LOG, allowing this function to return nullptr, and to change STATIC_DLSYM to tolerate this…",
